# Safety Rules

## AI System Safety
- LLM generates intents, NEVER executes directly
- All intents validated before action
- No direct database access from LLM output
- No raw file writes from AI-generated content
- Sanitize all LLM outputs before use

## Code Safety
- No secrets in code (use env vars)
- No hardcoded credentials
- Validate all external input
- Escape user content in templates
- Use parameterized queries only

## Execution Safety
- Lock groups prevent file conflicts in parallel execution
- Idempotency keys for all mutating operations
- Retry with backoff for transient failures
- Fail fast on validation errors
- Max recursion depth: 4 for spec splitting

## Webhook Safety
- Verify Stripe webhook signatures
- Idempotent event processing
- Handle duplicate events gracefully
